metadata.name: Care Free
metadata.description:
Cary's balcony had become something of a sanctuary after long days wandering about searching of... Well I hadn't figured that out just yet.

I began to daydream as the smoke off the end of my cigarette danced in the ocean breeze. The stress I had been "running" from seemed to float away into the distance with each tiny plume. Some people never get to experience this type of peace where, despite it all, you just decide that it's all okay and stop sweating the things you cant change. That's when I noticed the car approaching in the distance. The closer they got, the more I could feel their same sense of carefree peace I had discovered only moments before. 

Leica M7 + 35mm Summicron + Kodak Ektar 100
